      "content": "it's just so quiet. i'm looking at the map and i realize i don't want to book another leg of the journey. i don't want to find more cities or more landmarks. i just want to close the guidebook. it feels like if i just stop everything right here, in this moment, that everything would finally be settled and i wouldn't have to keep performing this traveler role anymore. does that make sense? that it's okay to just... call it a day?",
